It looks that usage of "default_operator" in search method of ElasticSearch client produces a following exception:

> elasticsearch.exceptions.RequestError: TransportError(400, 'illegal_argument_exception', 'request [/my_index/_search] contains unrecognized parameter: [default_operator]')

Without this option all works, of course with no necessary logics, using "OR" between boolean operands.
Code fragment:
`        search = es.search(
                index='my_index',
                _source=fields,
                request_timeout=600,
                size=5000,
                default_operator='AND',
                sort=['@timestamp'],
