Hi,

Simple question:  is it possible to use an other attribute than ID as primary key with SQLAlchemy plugin ?

It's seems to not be implemented yet : 

```python
class SQLAlchemyNode(six.with_metaclass(
        SQLAlchemyNodeMeta, NodeInstance)):

    class Meta:
        abstract = True

    @classmethod
    def get_node(cls, id, info=None):
        try:
            model = cls._meta.model
            query = get_query(model, info)
            instance = query.filter(model.id == id).one()
            return cls(instance)
        except NoResultFound:
            return None
```

If I understand this code correctly it seems that a node will always filter on the `id` attribute of the model. It would be realy nice and useful to have a meta information to set the identifier of a model for using other columns as primary key

